						               													<description>Book of Nox is a horror dungeon crawler which follows the adventures of a Group of Victorians exploring strange lands and battling a host of evil cultists and monsters in a traditional Victorian setting.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the setup of the game a story is chosen. (six included) The Games Master prepares the adventure. All the rooms and corridor cards are shuffled. The cards are revealed when a player explores the next doorway. &amp;#10;When a card is revealed dice are rolled to determine the encounters for that specific room.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A turn consists of three phases:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Players phase:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;During a turn a player must perform two actions (move, attack, push, swap weapons, put down/pick up lantern, open door).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Monsters phase&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After all players have acted, the monsters will attack. The monsters also perform two actions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Upkeep phase:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This is the tidy up phase, certain actions are resolved  now and it will state in the description when an action resolves in the upkeep phase.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is won if the players achieve the objective of the story.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
